Attributions and provenance
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project is an independent, clean-room reimplementation of publicly
documented QNX interfaces (the qconn target-agent wire protocol and the pdebug
DSMSG debug protocol) for interoperability. It contains no QNX source code and
no QNX SDK files.

The protocol understanding was derived and cross-checked from the following
public sources:

* rpdebug_qnx (rpdbg.py) — Mandiant
  https://github.com/mandiant/rpdebug_qnx
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  Used as a reference for the QNX pdebug DSMSG framing, checksum, and the
  process-memory-read message layout.

* qcl — Sasho Zbirov (zayfod)
  https://github.com/zayfod/qcl
  Licensed under the MIT License.
  Used as a reference for the qconn broker / launcher / file / cntl services
  and the overall wire protocol.

* QNX Neutrino public documentation (qnx.com developer docs) — the pdebug
  utility, the System Information perspective, and the sys/debug.h debug
  constants (e.g. _DEBUG_BREAK_*, _DEBUG_RUN_*) used as protocol facts.

* GNU GDB QNX Neutrino target support (GPL), including the 2003 gdb-patches
  submission adding the pdebug protocol, as a public description of the
  protocol. No GDB source was copied into this project.

* nmap qconn-exec.nse and the Metasploit qnx/qconn/qconn_exec module, as
  public descriptions of the qconn launcher exec behaviour.

